== 爭議 ==

===政治观点===
格里尔在2012年说，她是英国[[自由民主党_(英国)|自由民主党]]的成员。<ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/iplayer/episode/b01b3cdw/sign/Question_Time_19_01_2012/ ''Question Time''] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/iplayer/episode/b01b3cdw/sign/Question_Time_19_01_2012/ |date=20120124150342 }}, BBC, 19 January 2012.</ref>另外，从20世纪70年代至2000年代，她把自己形容为[[无政府主义者|无政府主义者]]或[[马克思主义者|马克思主义者]]。<ref>[http://www.takver.com/history/sydney/greer1972.htm "Greer on Revolution; Germaine on Love"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.takver.com/history/sydney/greer1972.htm |date=20191030114757 }}, ''Overland'', Nos. 50/51, Autumn 1972.</ref> 在2008年她形容自己是“一个老无政府主义者”，重申反对“等级制度和资本主义”是她政治的中心。白人種族歧視主義者。<ref>''Radio Mama'', 3CR Melbourne, 28 August 2008, 10:05 am EST.</ref>

=== 恐跨 ===
格里爾對[[跨性別女性|跨性別女性]]的立場自1997年以來就引起了爭議，當時她並沒有成功地反對[[劍橋大學紐納姆學院|劍橋大學紐納姆學院]]與物理學家[[拉克爾·帕德曼|拉克爾·帕德曼]]之間的聯繫，認為帕德曼出生性別為男性，因此不應該被錄取女子大學。<ref>{{cite news|author=Clare Garner|title=Fellows divided over don who breached last bastion|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/fellows-divided-over-don-who-breached-last-bastion-1257781.html|work=The Independent|date=1997-06-25|accessdate=2018-01-19|archive-date=2014-03-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140307162149/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/fellows-divided-over-don-who-breached-last-bastion-1257781.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>{{refn|group=n|An article by Clare Longrigg, "A Sister with No Fellow Feeling", alleging that Greer had outed Padman to the media, was published on 25 June 1997 by ''The Guardian''. The newspaper withdrew the allegation, apologized to Greer and made a donation at her request to the Newnham College Development Fund.<ref>{{cite web|author=Clare Longrigg with additional reporting by Laura Peek|title=When Germaine wants a job|work=The Guardian|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/19981201212018/http://www.pfc.org.uk/news/1997/gfolly02.htm|archivedate=1998-12-01|date=1997-06-25|url=http://www.pfc.org.uk/news/1997/gfolly02.htm|deadurl=yes|accessdate=2018-01-19}}</ref>}}2015年，[[威爾士卡迪夫大學|威爾士卡迪夫大學]]的學生請求阻止基爾在“女性與力量：20世紀的教訓”中在大學演講。學生們認為，她對跨性別女性的看法是恐跨和厭女的。基爾在接受英國廣播公司“新聞之夜”採訪時重申，她並不認為跨性別女性是女性。在同一次採訪中，基爾說，年度魅力女人提名[[凱特琳‧詹納|凱特琳‧詹納]]，這是一個[[厭女症|厭女症]]，詹納的故事的很大一部分是出於一種願望，卡戴珊 - 詹納家族的其他女性成員。基爾的評論受到跨性別喜劇演員[[麗貝卡‧根|麗貝卡‧魯特]]的譴責，她形容這些評論是“過時的”和“無禮的”，而拳擊發起人[[凱莉‧馬洛尼|凱莉‧馬洛尼]]要求基爾被起訴。<ref name="nytimes.com">Kimiko de Freytas-Tamura, [https://www.nytimes.com/2015/10/25/world/europe/cardiff-university-rejects-bid-to-bar-germaine-greer.html "Cardiff University Rejects Bid to Bar Germaine Greer"] {{Wayback|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/10/25/world/europe/cardiff-university-rejects-bid-to-bar-germaine-greer.html |date=20201224092830 }}, ''The New York Times'', 24 October 2015.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Gv2ACJAz_RA|title=YouTube|website=www.youtube.com|accessdate=2017-06-25|archive-date=2017-02-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170211063654/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Gv2ACJAz_RA|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.breitbart.com/london/2015/10/28/germaine-greer-punished-saying-trans-women-not-women-comments-like-holocaust-denial/|script-title=en:Germaine Greer ‘Should Be Punished’ For Saying Trans Women Not Women, And ‘Dragged’ Into Court|date=2015-10-28|publisher=|accessdate=2017-06-25|archive-date=2018-08-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180811164126/https://www.breitbart.com/london/2015/10/28/germaine-greer-punished-saying-trans-women-not-women-comments-like-holocaust-denial/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="nytimes.com"/> 講座按計劃進行。<ref>Steven Morris, [https://www.theguardian.com/books/2015/nov/18/transgender-activists-protest-germaine-greer-lecture-cardiff-university "Germaine Greer gives university lecture despite campaign to silence her"] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2015/nov/18/transgender-activists-protest-germaine-greer-lecture-cardiff-university |date=20210220103820 }}, ''The Guardian'', 18 November 2015.</ref> 基爾在2016年4月的一個澳大利亞問答集中再次重申了她的觀點，認為“男人”“決定”自己的性別是“不公平的”。令人厭惡的天主教壓迫者，支持性別歧視。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/apr/12/germaine-greer-tells-qa-her-trans-views-were-wrong-but-then-restates-them|title=Germaine Greer tells Q&A her trans views were wrong, but then restates them|first=Calla|last=Wahlquist|date=2016-04-11|publisher=|accessdate=2017-06-25|via=The Guardian|archive-date=2021-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208010422/https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/apr/12/germaine-greer-tells-qa-her-trans-views-were-wrong-but-then-restates-them|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 作品 ==
*(1970). ''The Female Eunuch'', London: MacGibbon & Kee.
*(1979). ''The Obstacle Race: The Fortunes of Women Painters and Their Work'', London: Martin Secker and Warburg.
*(1984). ''Sex and Destiny: The Politics of Human Fertility'', London: Harpercollins.
*(1986). ''Shakespeare'', Oxford: Oxford University Press (Past Masters series).
*(1986). ''The Madwoman's Underclothes:  Essays and Occasional Writings'', London: Picador.
*(1989). ''Daddy, We Hardly Knew You'', New York: Fawcett Columbine.
*(1989). with Susan Hastings, Jeslyn Medoff, Melinda Sansone (eds.), ''Kissing the Rod: An Anthology of Seventeenth Century Women's Verse'', London: Farrar, Straus and Giroux.
*(1991). ''The Change: Women, Ageing and the Menopause''.
*(ed.), ''The Uncollected Verse of Aphra Behn.
*(1995). ''Slip-Shod Sibyls: Recognition, Rejection and the Woman Poet''.
*with Ruth Little (eds.), ''The Collected Works of Katherine Philips, the Matchless Orinda'', Volume III, ''The Translations''.
*(1999). ''The Whole Woman'', London: Doubleday.
*with Susan Hastings (ed.), ''The Surviving Works of Anne Wharton''.
*(2000). ''John Wilmot, Earl of Rochester''. London: Northcote House Publishers.
*(2003). ''Poems for Gardeners'', London: Virago.
*(2003). ''The Beautiful Boy'', New York: Rizzoli.
*(ed.), ''101 Poems by 101 Women''.
*(2004). ''Whitefella Jump Up: The Shortest Way to Nationhood'', London: Profile Books (first published 2003 in ''Quarterly Essay'').
*(2007). ''Shakespeare's Wife'', London: Bloomsbury.
*(2013). ''White Beech: The Rainforest Years'', London: Bloomsbury.

